  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in the cumin, coriander, paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the chopped preserved lemon and cook for 2 minutes.",
    "Stir in the almond butter and cook for 2 minutes.",
    "Add 2 cups of water to the saucepan and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley or cilantro.",
    "Note: this recipe is for refrigerator pickling/preserving only — store in the refrigerator and consume within 1 week. Do not water-bath can without an acid (vinegar or lemon juice)."
